# Go Style

- Code must be `gofmt`-clean and pass `go vet` (CI enforces both).
- Keep the module dependency-light. Do not add a third-party dependency without a
  clear reason; prefer the standard library.
- Exported identifiers have doc comments. Comments explain intent/constraints,
  not the obvious.

```go
// ❌ BAD: narrates the code
i++ // increment i

// ✅ GOOD: explains a non-obvious constraint
// Deadline is deducted from the remaining request budget; retries do not reset it.
```

## Error handling

```go
// ❌ BAD: swallow
if err != nil { return }

// ✅ GOOD: wrap with context
if err != nil { return fmt.Errorf("load manifest %q: %w", path, err) }
```

- Never panic on request paths; recover at boundaries (hooks, event workers).
- Propagate `context.Context`; respect cancellation (client disconnect must stop
  upstream/OSS/image work).
